
<p>sorrows.  As <i>he</i> grows in age, may <i>he</i> grow in grace, and in<br/>the knowledge of his Savior Jesus Christ.  <i>Amen.</i></p>
<p><i>The Celebrant may then bless the family</i></p>
<p>May God the Father, who by Baptism adopts us as his<br/>children, grant you grace.  <i>Amen.</i></p>
<p>May God the Son, who sanctified a home at Nazareth, fill<br/>you with love.  <i>Amen.</i></p>
<p>May God the Holy Spirit, who has made the Church one<br/>family, keep you in peace.  <i>Amen.</i></p>
<p><i>The Peace may be exchanged.</i></p>
<p><i>The Minister of the Congregation is directed to instruct the people,<br/>from time to time, about the duty of Christian parents to make prudent<br/>provision for the well-being of their families, and of all persons to<br/>make wills, while they are in health, arranging for the disposal of<br/>their temporal goods, not neglecting, if they are able, to leave<br/>bequests for religious and charitable uses.</i></p>
    